  sodium: 1150 mg
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/balsamic-rosemary-turkey-meatloaves-5ffcaa305e2eea155c6b1979
author: Michelle Doll Olson
servings: 2
time required: 45 minutes
cuisine: Italian
---

Adjust rack to top position (middle and top positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%oz} into ½-inch pieces. Halve and peel @Yellow Onion{1}; grate one half on the largest holes of a #box grater{} (grate all the onion for 4). Transfer to a #large bowl{}. Peel and mince or grate half the @Garlic{1%clove} (keep remaining garlic whole). Strip rosemary leaves from stems; finely chop @Rosemary{¼%oz} leaves until you have 1 tsp (2 tsp for 4). Trim @Green Beans{6%oz} if necessary.

== Meatloaves ==

To bowl with grated onion, add @Ground Turkey{10%oz}, minced garlic, chopped rosemary, @Panko Breadcrumbs{¼%cup}, @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, and @Salt{¾%tsp} (for 4 servings, use 1 1/2 tsp salt). Season with @Pepper{} to taste, then mix to combine. Form into two 1-inch-tall loaves (for 4 servings, form into four loaves).

> TIP: Wet hands first to prevent turkey mixture from sticking while shaping.

Place on one side of a lightly oiled #baking sheet{} with @Vegetable Oil{1%tsp}. (For 4, spread meatloaves out across entire sheet.)

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Ketchup{4%tbsp} with @Balsamic Vinegar{2%tsp} (4 tsp for 4 servings), then brush onto tops of meatloaves. (Use the rest of the vinegar as you like.)

Bake on top rack for ~{15%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet then). (For 4, bake on middle rack.)

== Garlic Mashed Potatoes ==

Meanwhile, place potatoes and whole garlic in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until very tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes and garlic to #pot{}.

Mash with @Sour Cream{2%tbsp} and @Butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) until smooth and creamy, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season generously with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Cover to keep warm.

== Green Beans Amandine ==

Once meatloaves have baked 15 minutes, remove sheet from oven. Carefully toss green beans on empty side with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%tsp} and a pinch of salt and pepper.

> TIP: We recommend using tongs here.

(For 4 servings, leave meatloaves in oven and add green beans to a second sheet; roast on top rack.)

Return to top rack until meatloaves are cooked through and green beans are lightly browned, ~{10-12%minutes} more.

Sprinkle roasted green beans with @Almonds{½%oz}; toss to combine.

Divide meatloaves, green beans amandine, and garlic mashed potatoes between plates and serve.